-- Orix to Invest in Solar Power Projects, Tokyo Shimbun Says
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2012-08-17T01:26:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-17/orix-to-invest-in-solar-power-projects-tokyo-shimbun-says.html
Orix Corp. (8591) , a Japanese finance and
leasing company, will invest 54 billion yen ($680 million) to
develop solar power projects, the Tokyo Shimbun newspaper said,
citing President Makoto Inoue.  The investment will be made during the next three years to
develop plants and install panels on factory rooftops in  Japan 
with a total capacity of 200 megawatts, the newspaper cited
Inoue as saying.  The company may increase the investment to a total of 100
billion yen to build as much as 400 megawatts of capacity, Inoue
told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
 cwatanabe5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
